summary:
The issue was in `authMiddleware` in `/app/app/middleware.go`. The middleware was checking the raw request path (`r.URL.Path`) for the `/api/` prefix to determine if authentication was required. However, the router (`Router.ServeHTTP` in `main.go`) cleans the path using `path.Clean` before routing. This allowed attackers to bypass authentication by using paths like `//api/admin` or `/health/../api/admin`, which do not start with `/api/` (raw) but resolve to `/api/admin` after cleaning.

I fixed this by applying the same path cleaning logic in the middleware before checking the prefix.

